    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-01-17T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-01-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="1637"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1637">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 819.74/9.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">American Minister</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 25.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-01-17">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 17, 1912</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: The Department has received your No. 41 of the 3d
                    instant, in reply to its instruction of the 15th ultimo, to investigate and
                    report as to the wireless telegraphic systems proposed or already established on
                    the Isthmus of Panama.</p>
                <p>A copy of your dispatch has been sent to the Secretary of the Navy for his
                    information. In this connection a copy of a letter of the 11th instant from the
                    Secretary of the Navy is herewith inclosed.</p>
                <p>I am [etc.],</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">P. C. Knox.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
